    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's interesting how it's usually framed as this big win with the laws passing. but was it actually a success? i feel like some people say the whole nonviolent thing didnt even really change the core issues, or that the movement just got co-opted by the government. what's the actual deal with the results?",
